The leaves are an important source of nutrients, in addition they contain 17 amino acids and an adequate mineral composition (
 Hassan and Umar, 2006; 
 Talukdar and Hossain, 2014; 
 Wardhani et al., 2015; 
 Wang et al., 2016; 
 Nitu and Patidar, 2017). 
 M. balsamina is rich potassium, calcium, magnesium, sodium, phosphorus, manganese, zinc, and iron which contribute to prevent micronutrient deficiencies in human.
